# 👥 Contributor Guide

Welcome to the **Co‑Filming / Live Streaming Platform** project!  
This guide explains how contributors should work within the **System Management Protocol**.

---

## 1. Getting Started
- Clone the repo and set up your environment.  
- Review the **System Management Protocol** in `README.md`.  
- Join the team’s communication channel (Slack/Teams).  

---

## 2. Daily Workflow
- Check the **Daily Ops checklist** before starting work.  
- Log any incidents or anomalies in the issue tracker.  
- Use CI/CD pipelines for deployments — no manual pushes.  
- Document fixes and improvements clearly.  

---

## 3. Weekly Rhythm
- Attend Monday planning sync.  
- Contribute to load/stress testing on Wednesday.  
- Participate in Friday review and optimization.  
- Tag tasks with your role (e.g., Security, Cloud, DevOps).  

---

## 4. Monthly & Yearly
- Support roadmap updates and audits.  
- Join monthly release reviews.  
- Contribute to yearly strategic planning and product launches.  

---

## 5. Best Practices
- **Automation First:** Always prefer scripts/pipelines over manual work.  
- **Security by Design:** Encrypt data, follow firewall rules, respect compliance.  
- **Resilience:** Test backups, disaster recovery, and rollback mechanisms.  
- **Transparency:** Keep logs, issues, and documentation up to date.  

---

## 6. Incident Response
- Respond promptly to alerts (Slack/PagerDuty).  
- Rotate on‑call duties fairly.  
- Document every incident in the issue tracker.  
- Escalate critical issues to the Security Lead immediately.  

---

## 7. Contribution Rules
- Use **feature branches** for new work.  
- Submit **pull requests** with clear descriptions.  
- Request peer reviews before merging.  
- Follow coding standards and commit message guidelines.  

---

✅ This guide ensures every contributor knows how to align with the **System Management Protocol** and keep the platform reliable, secure, and scalable.

